'''''The Rolling Road of the Wayfarer''''' was a ballad penned by [[bard]] [[Belathra Baerlow]] in the early 15{{th}} century [[DR]].

{{quote|''Yet when peace reigns and men grow fat and proud<br/>And sneering and lazy and ever more loud<br/>Then do the rumors leap up and start to bubble<br/>And men talk of dark conspiracies, easy [[coin]], and trouble.''|An expert from the ''The Rolling Road of the Wayfarer.''}}
